700708f-a.text:
Castle Hill Ave., at East 177th Street (extreme right), showing W.P.A. workmen on a street repair job. The buildings are at the N.E. corner of the two thoroughfares, and the view is eastward along East
177th Street.
September 2, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
700708f-a.folder: Castle Hill Avenue & 177th Street (East), Bronx, NY

700227f-a.text:
E. 177th Street (foreground), at Castle Hill and Haviland Avenues, showing the triangular public place, built by the W.P.A. The low buildings, on the right, face on Castle Hill Avenue, which runs from right to left; and on the left, extending from the fore to the background, is Haviland Avenue. The apartment house is the Castle Garden
Apartments.
March 2, 1937
W.P.A.Photo
Five Boroughs Project
